    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with tin foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-haddock-pulusu-style-curry-and-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-haddock-pulusu-style-curry-and-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>onion wedges</strong>, <strong>curry powder </strong>and<strong> ground turmeric </strong>to the dish with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and <strong>tamarind paste</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-haddock-pulusu-style-curry-and-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white</strong> <strong>long grain</strong> <strong>rice</strong>, <strong>finely</strong> <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>,<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>and<strong> </strong>550ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[720ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[950ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>to the dish and stir it all together</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, put the dish in the oven and cook for 20-25 min, covered, or until the rice is almost cooked</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-haddock-pulusu-style-curry-and-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-haddock-pulusu-style-curry-and-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Chop any larger pieces of <strong>haddock</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-haddock-pulusu-style-curry-and-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is almost cooked, remove the dish from the oven and add your <strong>peas</strong>,<strong> spinach</strong> and <strong>haddock pieces </strong>and gently mix it all together</p><p>Return it to the oven for 7-8 min or until the fish is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-haddock-pulusu-style-curry-and-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> one-pot haddock pulusu-style curry & rice</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
